RepeatFinder as described in the paper "A clustering method for repeat analysis
in DNA sequences," by Natalia Volfovsky, Brian J. Haas, and Steven L. Salzberg.
Genome Biology 2:8 (2001), research0027.1-11.

See the file LICENSE for licensing terms.  This is open source
software.  

Copyright (c) 2001-2003 The Institute for Genomic Research, Rockville, MD.  All
rights reserved.

INPUT
-----
multifasta file

OUTPUT
------
1. AB.map.<id>.

ClassNumber  RepeatID  SeqID  Coord1 Coord2

    1          C1R1    Seq1       1     100

2. AB.mfasta.<id>.

multifasta file of actual repeat sequences

Title of each sequence is as follows

>RepeatID SeqID Coord1 Length Copies

OPTIONS and DEFAULT VALUES
--------------------------

-f <file in multiple-fasta format>

-r <minimal exact repeat length>

     DEFAULT  50

-g  <maximal gap for merging>

    (file:/home/natalia/web/Repeat_finder.html#brief)


    DEFAULT   25

-o  <overlap >

    DEFAULT   gap option

-e   <expect value for BLAST>

    DEFAULT 1e-8

-i   <identification name>

-d   <full path of scrap directory>

    DEFAULT  current directory

-v    <verbose>

    DEFAULT  yes



SRC
___

needs REPuter  http://BiBiServ.TechFak.Uni-Bielefeld.DE/reputer/

ABclass_search.cc  - update clusters after BLAST

Input files:  
R_map    -   results of the preliminary clustering
Qresult  -   results of BLAST search (pairs of similar classes)
seq.coord -  coordinates of assemblies


BBclass_search.cc  - clustering  "merging with overlap"
parameters:  -r <length of the minimal repeat> -o <overlap>
Input files: all.repeats - results from REPuter
             all.coord - non-duplicated all repeat coordinates
             seq.coord - coordinates of  assemblies

GBBclass_search.cc - clustering  "metging with gap"

parameters:  -r <length of the minimal repeat> -g <gap>
Input files: all.repeats - results from REPuter
             all.coord - non-duplicated all repeat coordinates
             seq.coord - coordinates of assemblies
















